<TEXT>
a man convicted in three date rapes 
involving three women he worked with at a restaurant was sentenced 
tuesday to up to 53 years in prison by a state judge who labeled 
him a sexual predator 
albany county judge w thomas keegan sentenced kenneth smyers 
28 of menands to 17 23 years to 53 years 
smyers was convicted dec 19 of one count each of rape and 
sexual abuse and two counts of sodomy 
before sentencing smyers proclaimed his innocence and asked 
why if he had committed such crimes it had taken the women 
involved so long to come forward and make complaints to authorities 
five women all coworkers at the albanyarea restaurant 
testified that smyers attacked them but some admitted they didnt 
tell authorities until several months later 
the jury acquitted smyers on one count each of rape and 
attempted sexual abuse in attacks on two of the women and of 
attempted rape on the woman he was convicted of sexually abusing 
assistant district attorney veronica dumas who prosecuted 
smyers said the stiff sentence sends a signal that date rape 
is a crime that wont be tolerated in the county 
he was convicted of four violent felonies and that sentence 
projects what those crimes are she said 
the incidents took place between october 1987 and july 1988 
prosecutors said 
according to testimony at smyers trial the attacks occurred 
under differing circumstances one woman said she voluntarily had 
sex with smyers but said a few days later he showed up at her 
apartment and forced himself on her over her objections 
another woman said she allowed smyers to sleep on her couch 
during a snowstorm but ended up having to fight him off he was 
convicted of sexual abuse in that incident 
several of the women said they continued to work and socialize 
with smyers after the incidents 
smyers attorney stephen coffey said he would appeal the 
conviction 
coffey said that smyers had a legitimate argument when he asked 
why it took so long for the women hes accused of attacking to come 
forward 
where were these women all this time why werent they 
saying anything he asked they were educated women why was it 
they were working with him and associating with him and with each 
other and not coming forward 
</TEXT>
