<TEXT>
a traffic stop escalated into gunfire and 
death for a young man tuesday in a confrontation between sheriffs 
deputies and several black muslims the second such incident this 
month 
the two deputies who made the earlymorning stop claimed they 
were surrounded by several men one of whom disarmed an officer 
that deputy pulled a backup weapon and fired several rounds 
striking and killing oliver beasley 27 who lived in an area west 
of suburban compton said sheriffs deputy chris wahla 
the two deputies were in a fight for their lives said 
sheriffs sgt steve van herpe the sergeant said deputies 
described several of the assailants as members of the nation of 
islam religious group 
neither deputy was hurt authorities did not identify them 
it was the second confrontation this month between black muslims 
and law enforcement officers both sparked by traffic stops 
residents of the neighborhood complained tuesday that deputies 
order black people to get out of their cars and lay spreadeagle on 
the street or stretch over the hood of their car for even routine 
stops a demand they contend is not made of whites 
while deputies conducted their investigation several people 
shouted angrily at them claiming some of the arrested men had been 
beaten while handcuffed a crowd was ordered to disperse at one 
point 
a man identified as david hartley 18 of culver city was 
wounded and later booked for attempted murder he was being treated 
in the jail ward of countyusc medical center listed in 
satisfactory condition with a shoulder wound 
five other men ranging in age from 15 to 35 also were arrested 
and booked for investigation of attempted murder following a 
nightlong search by of the neighborhood by deputies including a 
swat team 
the gun allegedly taken from the deputy was found on the 
stairwell of an apartment building where three of the men were 
arrested authorities said 
a man who answered a telephone call to nation of islam 
headquarters in los angeles on tuesday said no one will be 
making any comment until weve made a full investigation the 
man said the organization would hold a news conference in a day or 
two 
the fatal fight came a day after los angeles police department 
officials and nation of islam leaders met to discuss easing tense 
relations with law enforcement following a jan 3 street brawl 
between police and muslims that followed a traffic stop 
two dozen police officers and 13 nation of islam members were 
involved in a melee jan 3 in the southwest side of the city there 
were injuries on both sides 
police claim one of the muslims interfered with the arrest 
process then attacked officers when they tried to arrest him 
companions ran out of cars and joined the fray 
six muslims attended mondays meeting 
ive been with the nation for 32 years and i know of no other 
time when muslims and police have sat down and talked on this 
level said wali muhammad head of the western branch of the 
fruit of islam the nation of islams security detail 
the police department is conducting an internal investigation of 
allegations that officers started the brawl 
