<TEXT>
the leader of colombias notorious 
medellin cocaine cartel has written to a bogota newspaper saying he 
wants to set them straight on a story he still runs the cartel and 
his friends havent deserted him 
my freedom is the best proof i have to show the country that 
the people are not selling me out and that my friends are neither 
abandoning nor betraying me pablo escobar wrote 
an article monday in el tiempo quoted security force officials 
as saying escobars principal allies were abandoning him as police 
and the military moved in pursuing an allout drug war by the 
government of president virgilio barco escobar wrote on tuesday to 
el tiempo publisher hernando santos castillo saying he was still 
in control of the most powerful drug operation in colombia and that 
it stood together in its decision to seek peace with the government 
the letter carried escobars signature and bore what was 
apparently the imprint of his index finger to prove the document 
was genuine the document was also sent to other news media 
escobar who heads the countrys most wanted list with a 
500000 deadoralive price on his head also said the medellin 
cartel would keep up its war against the rival cali cartel based 
to the south of medellin 
he said jorge valasquez a member of the cali cartel gave 
information to police that resulted in their killing of gonzalo 
rodriguez gacha in a shootout on dec 15 rodriguez gacha was 
escobars close associate and a man considered the most violent of 
the medellin drug lords 
escobar said the entire cartel was behind a peace offer made by 
its leaders last week to barcos government asking for 
constitutional and legal guarantees in exchange for the 
cartels agreeing to give up the cocaine business stop its 
campaign of violence and free its hostages 
the cartel is reckoned to still hold 16 people after freeing 
five recently 
escobars letter indicated the cartel still will demand an end 
to extradition however 
the barco government has packed off 13 trafficking suspects to 
the united states since it intensified its drug war in august the 
drug traffickers replied with a terror campaign that has claimed 
the lives of 209 people and included the bombing a colombian 
airliner 
escobar indicated there was no disagreement within the cartel 
over the peace offer which the government has refused to accept 
saying drug bosses who surrender will have to answer in court for 
their crimes 
his letter read if the colombian government someday decides 
to fight for the peace of our nation in a sovereign and courageous 
way it will find an interminable list of extradition candidates 
drug traffickers hired assassins and paramilitary forces that want 
to join it in the process 
military forces said on tuesday they were taking whatever 
measures were necessary to protect president bush from escobar and 
other drug barons when bush attends an antidrug summit in cartagena 
on feb 15 
us authorities have reportedly said traffickers are preparing 
an attempt on bushs life in the five hours he will be in cartagena 
bush barco president jaime paz zamora of bolivia and possibly 
president alan garcia of peru are to discuss cooperation in the 
fight against drugs 
garcias participation was not certain he said he would not 
attend while us invasion troops remained in panama 
