snow in the nations breadbasket is raising 
prospects for the 1990 winter wheat crop according to the 
governments joint agricultural weather facility 
the facility is operated by the commerce and agriculture 
departments and reported tuesday on crop and weather conditions for 
the week of jan 1420 
precipitation fell in the great plains from texas to central 
nebraska providing muchneeded snow cover and moisture to the 
winter wheat crop the report said the moderate temperatures 
and moisture were beneficial to livestock producers as they helped 
pastures 
however the report added wheat farmers and fruit growers were 
concerned that the warm weather will start growth too soon 
leaving these crops more vulnerable to a hard freeze later on 
the report said the heavy wet snow in the plains was the first 
moisture of the season for many stressed dryland fields of wheat 
livestock was responding favorably to abovenormal 
temperatures the report said texas ranges and pastures were 
showing some signs of improvement as mild weather and moisture 
returned to most areas 
pastures in oklahoma were greening although heavier 
supplemental feeding of livestock was necessary in areas of the 
central plains because of snow cover 
lambing and calving activity was increasing in michigan and 
idaho the report said florida pastures were mostly 
fairtogood in the panhandle and northern peninsula and fair in 
