state lt gen prosper avril 
an information ministry statement told broadcasters that it must 
approve their local news reports and ordered them to refrain 
from relaying or broadcasting any information on haiti from 
stations broadcasting from abroad 
in recent days stations have relayed statements by exiled 
opposition leaders broadcast by radio france internationale and the 
voice of america 
stations also were told not to broadcast anything likely to 
incite agitation 
radio is the main source of information in this impoverished 
caribbean nation which shares the island of hispaniola with the 
dominican republic haiti has two tv stations one governmentowned 
and the other in private hands 
