government television tuesday night that the political leaders 
expelled and militants beaten and arrested over the weekend 
maintained a climate of tension and poisoned the atmosphere 
relatives said police on tuesday arrested antoine izmery 45 
one of haitis main importers and a vocal critic of the government 
of president avril telling him he would be forced into exile 
izmery was arrested while driving to work police searched his 
downtown warehouse and went to his home for his passport his wife 
said 
the government declared a 30day state of siege and beat and 
arrested dozens of militants and prominent politicians on saturday 
