i was doubtful this day would ever come 
at the church brandley bowed his head and exclaimed amen 
as the rev leroy ross thanked god saying you have indeed freed 
an innocent man from execution and after nine and a half years of 
being on death row 
montgomery county district attorney peter speers said he will 
ask the us supreme court to review the case but wouldnt seek 
another trial if the high court refused 
speers said he still believes brandley is guilty of the murder 
of cheryl dee fergeson slain while attending a volleyball 
tournament at the houstonarea high school where brandley worked as 
a janitor 
brandleys first trial ended in a hung jury and an allwhite 
jury convicted him of capital murder in his second trial 
a third trial would be virtually impossible because of the time 
that has elapsed lost evidence and corrupted witnesses speers 
said 
brandleys attorneys have claimed their client was the victim of 
racism brandley is black and miss fergeson was white 
as much as wed like to think this is the 1980s or 1990s and 
racial prejudices are behind us race was a major factor in the 
prosecution and the investigation said defense attorney paul 
nugent 
in 1987 a judge recommended a third trial because the two 
others had been discriminatory on dec 13 the states high court 
agreed saying the investigation lacked the rudiments of 
fairness 
evidence revealed during the 1987 hearing showed contradictory 
testimony from other janitors all of whom were white 
texas attorney general jim mattox said he would not join speers 
in seeking the us supreme court ruling because the original trial 
was racially tainted 
cl buck fergeson the slain girls father said he was 
upset that brandley was free im still convinced hes guilty 
and i hope speers is going to do everything he can to rectify the 
situation 
the janitor who found miss fergesons body henry peace was 
