<TEXT>
the drug rehabilitation center 
treating marion barry stresses physical and spiritual recovery 
through a method largely developed by alcoholics anonymous 
its also a place where tears are inevitable one graduate of 
the program said 
the mayor of washington dc checked into the hanleyhazelden 
center on monday lurma rackley a spokeswoman for the mayor said 
details about his health would be kept private but the most 
serious problem is alcoholism 
the 66bed nonprofit clinic opened in 1986 as a satellite unit 
of the hazelden foundation in center city minn treatment 
generally lasts 28 days and costs about 7500 
the foundation wont reveal the names of current or former 
patients but famous figures who have said they spent time at the 
minnesota clinic include kitty dukakis wife of massachusetts gov 
michael dukakis former washington redskins player dexter manley 
and designer calvin klein 
the weeks after detoxification are difficult but bearable said 
bill hetland a graduate of the minnesota clinic 
youre in such a frame of mind it doesnt take much to get 
the people to cry he said 
the program near minneapolis was founded 40 years ago by a group 
of alcoholics anonymous members and businessmen concerned about 
alcoholism among employees and relatives 
its goal according to a center pamphlet is to help 
chemically dependent people break through denial and to maintain 
ongoing abstinence and recovery upon return to the community 
depending on the severity of the addiction patients spend the 
first day to one week in detoxification in a hospitallike setting 
then the patient is moved to treatment wards where men and 
women are kept separate each ward holds about 20 people 
you can have visitors said brenda lyles a former official 
in the state department of health and rehabilitative services who 
was involved in licensing the west palm beach center you arent 
confined there in the sense that you arent locked down the 
expectation is that you desire to be there for your own treatment 
the day usually begins by 7 am 
patients are assigned chores such as vacuuming and room 
inspections before breakfast the rest of the day is spent watching 
films or listening to lectures 
after each session patients return to smaller groups for 
processing going over the content of the days lesson all 
patients keep journals 
the rooms contain single beds and white formica dressers 
television is allowed only during certain hours and phone calls 
are discouraged 
the entrance to the centers sixacre campus has a string of 
signs with sayings that include let go and let god and one 
day at a time the motto of alcoholics anonymous 
state substanceabuse experts praise the hanleyhazelden center 
they have a long record of excellence said john daigel 
