<TEXT>
defense minister italo luder 
abruptly resigned today after the army chief of staff met with 
president carlos menem without informing him 
i gave the president my undeclinable resignation luder 73 
told reporters after a halfhour meeting with menem at government 
house 
it was the latest crisis facing menems government which has 
been beset by economic and military problems since he took office 
in july 
menem told reporters he had not decided whether to accept what 
would be the third cabinet resignation since he took office but 
the president indicated he sided with the army chief gen isidro 
caceres in the dispute 
luder imposed an unspecified sanction on caceres on tuesday 
its very possible that by this afternoon i will lift the 
sanction menem said i think in this aspect dr luder was not 
in full knowledge of the facts he did not elaborate 
caceres met privately with menem and interior minister julio 
mera figueroa on jan 17 and discussed matters of internal 
security luder said he too should have been invited 
asked why he wasnt he said in an interview broadcast this 
morning by radio mitre i dont know 
when i called him caceres the next day he didnt give a 
satisfactory explanation said luder a lawyer and career 
politician 
neither menem nor luder specified caceres sanction but it 
could have ranged from a disciplinary hearing to arrest in any 
event caceres almost certainly would have been forced to resign 
an army expert said 
there was no immediate response from caceres who helped the 
government of thenpresident raul alfonsin put down the villa 
martelli army insurrection led by then col mohammed seineldin in 
december 1988 
though the uprising was quelled and seineldin forced into 
retirement the army remains divided between a nationalist sector 
that wants a greater say in politics and the sector led by caceres 
that has stayed out of politics 
we believe that the solution to argentinas problems should 
come from the political parties the political leaders 
caceres said last month 
luders resignation comes at a time when the government has 
failed to solve several problems in the military including low pay 
for soldiers poor equipment and a budget so small that the number 
of conscripts this year was reduced 
there was little indication beforehand that luder and caceres 
were at odds although caceres had complained about the militarys 
low budget and had spoken of the climate of social unrest in this 
south american country that is beset by inflation and recession 
also caceres publicly called for the release from prison of 
four former commanders of the military juntas that ruled argentina 
from 1976 to 1983 
two former presidents and generals jorge videla and roberto 
