<TEXT>
president bush saying that environmental 
challenges are so important that they must be addressed at the 
highest level of government today endorsed elevating the 
environmental protection agency to a cabinetlevel department of 
the environment 
at a news conference in the white house briefing room the 
president backed legislation that has been introduced in congress 
with bipartisan support 
i am convinced that cabinet status will help influence the 
worlds environmental policies he said noting that many nations 
have environmental ministries 
bushs announcement represented a switch in his attitude toward 
creating a new cabinet department during his first year in office 
he had opposed expansion of the cabinet 
the epa an independent regulatory agency created in 1970 to 
enforce environmental laws would become the 15th cabinet agency 
the president met with sponsors of the legislation before 
announcing his endorsement and said he would work with congress to 
draft acceptable legislation 
bush made the announcement in an opening statement in which he 
touched on a wide range of topics 
ive decided that the environmental challenges that face 
america and the world are so important that they must be addressed 
at the highest level of government he said 
bush said epa now headed by administrator william reilly is 
one of the largest and most important regulatory agencies in the 
government and called elevation of it to cabinet status another 
step forward in support of conservation and environmental 
protection 
reilly said the elevation of epa is an important environmental 
milestone 
leaders of the house and senate government operations committees 
introduced bipartisan legislation tuesday that would create a 
department of the environment and make the epa administrator part 
of the cabinet as environmental secretary 
similar legislation has been introduced in the past but made 
little headway without support from the white house 
sen john glenn dohio chairman of the senate government 
operations committee said the epa as a regulatory agency without 
cabinet status doesnt send the appropriate signal to the rest of 
the world at a time when critical environmental issues are global 
in nature 
environmental concerns have induced every major industrialized 
nation to create a ministerial post for environmental protection 
with the only exception being the united states said glenn at a 
news conference 
sen william roth rdel another cosponsor and the ranking gop 
member on the committee called raising the epas status a first 
step to reorganizing government to face the problems of the 90s 
and the first problems of the 21st century 
in the house rep john conyers dmich chairman of the house 
government operations committee promised to push the epa bill to 
the floor as quickly as possible and said he hoped legislation 
could be ready for the presidents signature by the 20th 
anniversary of earth day in late april 
