for the media almost 400 children were alleged to have been 
molested at mcmartin eight people were originally charged and 
there were more than 50 uncharged suspects in a case that 
reportedly involved a kiddie porn ring a satanic cult animals 
mutilations and torture 
in the end however there were just two defendants raymond 
buckey and his mother peggy mcmartin buckey 
after the verdicts a few jurors said that while they believed 
that some molestations occurred at mcmartin the prosecution failed 
to prove where when and by whom the prosecution in effect had 
failed and failed miserably 
media critic david shaw says the mcmartin story exposed 
several basic flaws in the way contemporary news organizations 
function pack journalism vigilantism laziness superficiality 
cozy relationships with prosecutors a competitive zeal that sends 
reporters off in a frantic search to be first with the latest 
shocking allegation responsible journalism be damned 
shaw may never get a conviction on those charges but it seems 
clear that shoddy workmanship can be traced to many professions in 
the mcmartin case and that the nations longest and costliest trial 
will be remembered for little else 
