a man who set fire to his son seven years ago 
was paroled today under a veil of secrecy and orders to wear an 
electronic leash and stay away from the boy who is keeping a bb 
gun handy just in case 
charles rothenberg is out on parole and he has reached his 
destination said tipton kindel spokesman for the state 
corrections department 
rothenberg wearing an electronic device that will enable 
authorities to monitor his movements left prison shortly after 
midnight kindel said adding that rothenberg is now the 
mostwatched parolee in california history 
david rothenberg who is now 13 said he was frightened by his 
fathers release and keeps a pellet gun by his bed just in case 
id shoot his eye out if he ever came over id blind him he 
said in a recent interview 
the boy was severely disfigured by the fire set by his father in 
a custody dispute with his estranged wife 
prison officials were determined to keep rothenbergs 
whereabouts secret during his threeyear parole and wouldnt even 
confirm he was paroled within the united states 
earlier today on nbcs today show kindel said rothenberg 
will be under the strictest parole ever for a california 
parolee 
he will not be allowed to leave the jurisdiction to which he 
is being paroled he will not be able to go to the county where his 
son lives he will not be allowed to have any contact with his son 
his exwife or her current husband kindel said 
if rothenberg violates parole he will be returned to prison for 
up to a year 
david lives in orange county with his mother marie and 
stepfather police officer richard hafdahl who helped in the 
investigation of the fire 
asked on today what is being done to protect david kindel 
said that if rothenberg is ever not where hes supposed to be 
then the family david will be notified immediately 
rothenberg 49 set fire to his son in a buena park motel room 
in 1983 after a telephone argument in which his estranged wife said 
rothenberg would not be able to see the boy again 
rothenberg had taken the boy on a holiday to southern california 
from new york where the boy was living with his mother 
if i cant have him nobody else can rothenberg said when 
arrested six days later he told authorities he was going to kill 
himself but was too much of a coward 
david dragged from the inferno by motel guests suffered 
thirddegree burns over 90 percent of his body 
rothenberg was convicted of attempted murder arson and other 
charges and got the maximum a 13year prison term the sentence 
was cut in half because of good behavior 
if he had been convicted today rothenberg would have faced up 
to life in prison 
in a letter last month to the los angeles times rothenberg 
called his own release an unforgivable act 
prison officials kept the relocation plans secret fearing a 
repeat of the hysteria surrounding the 1987 release of larry 
singleton 
singleton who had raped a teenager and left her for dead after 
hacking off her forearms with an ax had to be moved repeatedly 
from northern california communities where he was rejected by an 
outraged public 
kindel acknowledged in the today interview that if 
rothenbergs location is revealed it could be a problem for the 
corrections department and said another highprofile parolee 
an apparent reference to singleton cost the state more than 2 
million to move him from location to location 
were hoping to convince the public that not only is its 
safety assured but so is the safety of david rothenburg so that 
perhaps they will simply ignore this man and shun him and not give 
