<TEXT>
a van carrying migrant farm workers ran 
off a foggy rural road and plunged into a murky canal today 
drowning 10 people and injuring two authorities said 
the driver and a frontseat passenger crawled out of the 
submerged van through windows sheriffs deputies dived into the 12 
feet of water but were unable to rescue the others trapped inside 
said lt bill chamness 
some of them had stuck their arms out trying to get out but 
they just didnt make it he said when the deputies dove in to 
get them they were already dead 
the privately owned van carrying 12 mexican migrant workers ran 
off the road at a curve near this farm community about 100 miles 
northwest of miami chamness said 
the road cuts through a sugar cane district intersected by 
numerous irrigation and drainage canals 
we think it was probably due to dense fog chamness said 
evidently they got on the curve quicker than they thought and 
instead of turning they went straight into the canal 
the survivors both men were taken to hendry general hospital 
with minor injuries such as scrapes and bruises and showed no 
immediate signs of broken bones or internal injuries said 
emergency room nurse maggie kocher 
the driver was admitted in stable condition for observation and 
the passenger was treated and was to be released she said 
the sheriffs office didnt receive word of the 730 am crash 
until 746 am authorities said a sheriffs diver who attached a 
towtruck cable to the back of the van estimated visibility in the 
canal at 2 feet chamness said 
