supporters of imprisoned political extremist lyndon larouche from 
the democratic primary ballot 
the board in a 71 vote agreed with a finding by its hearing 
officer that the slate of five prolarouche candidates had only 
3865 valid signatures of the required 5000 to get on the ballot 
for the election in march 
