president elias hrawi will create a crack 
security force to combat terrorism in west beirut and encourage 
foreign diplomats to return to the citys moslem sector a military 
source said wednesday 
also on wednesday rival shiite moslem militias dueled with 
howitzers and rocket launchers in southern lebanon and police said 
one person was killed and another injured 
the renewed fighting in iqlim altuffah ended a 16day relative 
lull in the latest round of clashes between the proiranian shiite 
hezbollah or party of god and the shiite amal militia by police 
count 98 people have been killed and 279 wounded since dec 23 
no advances were reported by either side said a police 
spokesman who cannot be identified in line with standing rules 
the military source who spoke on condition of anonymity said 
the new security force for west beirut will be made up of 400 men 
drawn from the elite combat forces of the army and police 
hrawi said tuesday that west beirut would become a security 
oasis under the security force 
all western diplomatic missions have left the city since 
mid1984 because of terrorist attacks and kidnappings of 
foreigners most of the acts were blamed on shiite moslem 
underground factions affiliated with hezbollah 
in all 18 foreigners including eight americans are missing 
and believed held hostage the longestheld is terry anderson 
chief middle east correspondent for the associated press kidnapped 
in west beirut on march 16 1985 
asked whether the proposed security plan would also cover the 
slums of south beirut a hezbollah stronghold where most of the 
