most probably south beirut will be included he refused to 
elaborate 
he said all militias will be banned from west beirut as part of 
the plan and that the commando squad will be trained on special 
assignments and might be equipped with helicopters for raid 
intervention in case it is needed to deal with special and 
sensitive assignments such as protecting foreign diplomats 
the source said a 3000man brigade from hrawis 22000member 
army will deploy in west beirut in the first stage of the security 
plan 
according to the source the security plan also calls for a 
gradual withdrawal of syrian troops from west beirut 
hrawi and syrian president hafez assad discussed the plan in 
three days of talks in damascus that ended tuesday 
