tuesday that ending the standoff over who runs lebanons government 
was a priority 
if at the end there is no alternative i shall use force 
hrawi said i will use everything to stop the partition 
assad said he would commit whatever forces hrawi needed to oust 
aoun 
syria is the main power broker in lebanon by dint of the 40000 
troops it has stationed there they were deployed under a 1978 arab 
league peacekeeping mandate and syria has rejected aouns demands 
that they be withdrawn 
hrawi was elected president under an arab leaguebrokered plan 
to end lebanons 14yearold civil war aoun rejected the plan 
because it does not specifically call for syrias withdrawal or 
give a timetable 
he recently ordered lebanons media not to refer to hrawi as 
president the nations seven daily newspapers did not publish 
wednesday due to a strike called tuesday by a press group to 
protest aouns attempts to censor the media 
