the statues survived the destalinization campaign that saw 
thousands of similar monuments dismantled across the communist 
world because czechoslovak authorities were slow to take up the 
policy adopted in the soviet union after 1956 
a giant statue of stalin that once dominated central prague was 
dismantled only in the early 1960s 
