congressional analysts said wednesday 
congressional budget office director robert d reischauer also 
projected that the us economy would sidestep a recession this 
year and he predicted that congress would be hard pressed to plug 
the huge budget gap sen daniel moynihans proposed social security 
payroll tax cut would create 
in remarks that came five days before president bush reveals his 
1991 budget reischauer said a healthy economy would not be enough 
to allay the governments persistent fiscal woes 
over the next few years no further progress in reducing the 
