pentagon announced wednesday 
cheney in a statement said he was forced to take the 
costsaving step in light of the coming changes in the force 
structure and disposition of the us armed forces 
several weeks ago cheney ordered a freeze on hiring civilian 
dod workers in a similar effort to trim spending 
the moratorium on construction contracts goes into effect 
immediately and lasts until april 30 
it applies to the award of all new military construction 
contracts including those for architectural and engineering design 
services the statement said 
the pentagons fiscal 1990 military construction budget as 
approved by congress amounted to around 85 billion the bill made 
wholesale cuts in president bushs request for foreign bases but 
added millions of dollars for domestic installations 
the statement said the only exceptions are those contracts and 
options excercised 
