stealth bomber for its radarevading design at 530 million a 
copy the aircraft has been attacked by many members of congress as 
too expensive at least if the air force buys all 132 it wants 
while the changing soviet empire is good news for the west 
perle said it would be foolish for the united states to dismantle 
its defenses precipitiously 
we would be wise to wait a little longer before confidently 
predicting that we can afford to be weak in the face of 
uncertainty he said 
the soviet union spend as much as 20 percent of its gross 
national product on defense compared with 6 percent by the united 
states he said 
as for the strategic defense initiative known as star wars 
perle said the concept of a shield to protect the nation from all 
enemy missiles is unrealistic 
at the same time he said a serious program of research and 
development oriented towards a partial shield can and should go 
forward even in the face of shrinking defense budgets 
as the prospect of nuclear proliferation draws closer we 
should be reminded that the threat is neither exclusively soviet 
nor for that matter exclusively deliberate there are third 
countries and there are accidents and these two reasons alone would 
justify a vigorous research and development program perle said 
