west germany said wednesday that 
a concrete warning about possible terrorists aboard a libyan 
airliner prompted its police to hold and search the aircraft for 
hours at frankfurt airport 
the action tuesday drew a strong protest from col moammar 
gadhafis libyan government 
the libyan arab airlines plane was allowed to return to tripoli 
wednesday 
border police detained and searched the boeing 727 at frankfurt 
tuesday shortly after it arrived from the libyan capital with 75 
passengers plus crew 
chief government spokesman hans klein refused to divulge the 
source of the concrete warning he said triggered the action and 
would not say if it was a foreign intelligence service 
federal security officials speaking on condition of anonymity 
said there was a tip terrorists might have been aboard 
interior ministry spokesman roland bachmeier told reporters 
three armed men were detained for carrying weapons without permits 
but were released after they turned out to be the airlines 
security guards 
bachmeier defended the governments actions saying west germany 
must take seriously such a warning he said any other eaction 
would be gross negligence and contrary to duty 
he denied libyan allegations that passengers were mistreated by 
police 
police detained and searched the plane shortly after it landed 
in frankfurt at 349 pm tuesday all luggage was closely 
inspected 
the search lasted until 945 pm but the captain refused to 
take off without the three guards who had been detained bachmeier 
said 
the jetliner left for tripoli at 1106 am tuesday frankfurt 
airport spokesman wolfgang schwalm said 
the libyan news agency jana monitored in london quoted the 
planes captain as saying after the aircraft returned to libya that 
german authorities ordered a search of the plane without offering 
any explanation 
jana quoted him as saying passengers were searched most of 
whom were women children and sick people 
