and international economic cooperation said at a news conference 
that changes in eastern europe are requiring large amounts of 
resources necessary for them to get out of their present 
quandry 
but he said un officials believe problems facing developing 
countries remain the most important concerns in efforts toward 
international economic development 
it is to be expected since these countries do have a large 
pool of welltrained professionals and technicians that they 
should be on their feet economically speaking relatively quickly 
