we hope that they will be able also to provide markets for 
commodities from developing countries and also join the western 
developed countries in providing official development assistance 
for countries mainly in africa which need it 
a un report on economic development released wednesday said 
world economic growth and the average increase in per capita income 
in the 1980s were the lowest in three decades 
according to the report developing countries have suffered the 
most because of the decline in growth with many people there worse 
off in 1990 than they were in 1980 
some developing countries in asia however achieved steady 
income increases the past decade the report cited china and india 
the two most populous lowincome countries as having improved 
their economic conditions during the 1980s 
but many countries particularly in africa and latin america 
experienced a collapse in commodity prices the past decade while 
facing mounting indebtedness inadequate funds from foreign sources 
and falling income levels the report said 
in addition increased protectionism eroded trade for the 
developing countries the report said 
particular attention should be given to commoditydependent 
economies who are already under pressure as a result of their 
structural rigidities debtservicing difficulties and the 
inadequacy of development finance international financial flows to 
developing countries are regarded as an important catalytic device 
in the development process the report said 
the united nations will convene a special session on economic 
development on feb 26 
