a diabetic woman who felt god had a 
purpose for the infant doctors wanted her to abort has taken her 
newborn home from the hospital but not before both fought a 
battle for their lives 
deborah jennings 22 was warned at an early age never to have 
children when she became pregnant doctors urged her for the sake 
of her health to abort the baby 
the doctors wanted me to get rid of it she said tuesday as 
she and her 8pound 9ounce son billy oneal prepared to leave 
spartanburg regional medical center i told them that god had a 
purpose for this baby 
diabetic women are more likely than nondiabetic women to give 
birth to babies that are stillborn suffer deformities or weigh 
less said hosptial spokeswoman debbie dalhouse also pregnancy 
puts a great deal of stress on a diabetic woman her insulin level 
may fluctuate widely and she is more likely to suffer 
complications during pregnancy and delivery 
during miss jennings pregnancy she was hospitalized six times 
once for more than two weeks 
when she went into labor jan 16 some amniotic fluid escaped 
and blocked one of her blood vessels resulting in cardiac arrest 
her heart stopped for four minutes 
as one team of doctors worked to resuscitate miss jennings 
another delivered the baby by cesarean section the medical staff 
forced oxygen into the infants lungs for five minutes until the 
baby began breathing on his own 
although miss jenningss heart eventually began beating again 
the new mother lay in a coma suspended between life and death 
doctors didnt give the family much hope 
they told us if she didnt respond in 48 hours she would 
never respond said betty jennings miss jennings mother 
for miss jennings the two days were a nightmare from within 
her motionless body she could feel and hear even see but she 
could not respond 
i could hear everybody talking she said you could hear 
what they were saying but you couldnt respond no matter what you 
did you couldnt respond 
throughout the ordeal nurses would ask miss jennings to show 
some sign of life squeeze a hand raise an eyebrow respond in 
some way inside miss jennings said i was squeezing her hand 
talking to her hollering at her but it wasnt coming out i was 
