international committee of the red cross icrc to airlift relief 
supplies to governmentheld juba and areas controlled by the rebel 
sudan peoples liberation army 
the concerned authorities have authorized the icrc to ferry 
reief materials to juba area and even to those areas where the 
rebels are present if it the icrc wanted to do so shummo said 
in a statement distributed by the official sudan news agency 
the government suspended relief flights to south sudan last 
august to guarantee the safety of relief workers after the collapse 
of a ceasefire in fighting between the government and rebel forces 
that took up arms in 1983 to demand greater autonomy and economic 
reforms 
