1500 tons of sorghum from muglad in the south to aweil in the bahr 
al ghazal region 
he said the relief train will operate flying the un flag and 
will distribute part of its supplies at rebelheld areas 
in new york a un official familiar with relief operations in 
south sudan said meanwhile that heightened fighting in the region 
is interrupting attempts to move in supplies that agencies expect 
will be needed by june 
