prince norodom sihanouk of cambodia said 
wednesday he was quitting again as head of the resistance coalition 
battling cambodias vietnamesebacked government 
the exiled chief of state said his resignation is in protest of 
foreign accusations that he is an accomplice in the communist khmer 
rouges drive to regain power in cambodia disputes with his 
coalition partners caused him to step down several times before 
he said he would stop meeting with most foreign diplomats and 
reporters and would not attend any international conferences on the 
cambodian situation sihanouk said he will run for president if a 
political situation is worked out and general elections are held 
sihanouk a noncommunist has headed a resistance coalition 
that also includes the communist khmer rouge and the noncommunist 
khmer peoples national liberation front 
the khmer rouge which conducted a reign of terror in cambodia 
from 1975 until early 1979 in which 1 million people died when it 
was ousted by vietnam is militarily the strongest of the three 
factions 
the khmer rouge has claimed major battle victories since 
september when vietnam said it pulled the last of its troops from 
cambodia the victories have raised fears the khmer rouge could 
rule again 
sihanouk always had an uneasy relationship with the khmer rouge 
but insisted that the only way to contain the group was to include 
it in any political settlement 
in his statement sihanouk said he would retain the title of 
chief of state of cambodia that he held before being ousted in a 
1970 coup led by the usbacked lon nol he said the lon nol 
government was illegal and thus his old title is still in effect 
he said that after several scheduled appointments over the next 
few weeks he will stop meeting all foreign officials diplomats and 
journalists the exceptions are to be his friends from china 
and north korea the two countries where he lives most of the year 
in his statement sinhanouk said without elaborating that 
certain governments of the free world in addition to 
journalists intellectuals and parliamentarians have decided to 
attack me and accuse me of complicity with the khmer rouge 
he did not defend his alliance with the group 
sihanouk is still widely revered in his homeland and is believed 
to be the one person who could hold the country together 
sihanouk has given qualified support to an australian proposal 
to dismantle both the resistance and the vietnaminstalled 
government and set up an interim un administration to run the 
country and prepare for a general election 
in another development a un official said wednesday that 
khmer rouge guerrillas moved nearly all the refugees from a united 
nationsaided borai camp toward the thaicambodian border closer 
to the fighting 
the communist fighters apparently wanted to prevent un 
officials from transferring them to nearby site k a new camp that 
is safer and has better medical and other services but is not khmer 
rougecontrolled 
only about 200 refugees remained at borai wednesday afternoon 
said patrick van de velde deputy director of the un border 
relief operation after a visit there 
borai originally housed up to 4500 people but threefourths of 
them have been moved toward the border since jan 15 said an aid 
official speaking on condition of anonymity 
