wall street is turning into mean street for the 
nations big brokerages and even leaner regional firms are 
struggling to cope with an exodus of small investors since the 1987 
stock market crash 
a slumping stock market declining corporate takeover activity 
and faltering junk bonds point to a continuing industry shakeout 
that analysts say will mean more cuts in businesses and jobs 
the trend was dramatized by merrill lynch amp cos stunning 
