the new york mercantile exchange and the 
commodity exchange inc said today they would pursue merger 
negotiations and announced the formation of a joint board that 
would govern a consolidated entity 
the exchanges issued a statement saying that the executive 
committees from nymex and comex met tuesday and agreed to form the 
joint governing board 
the exchanges also said the respective boards instructed their 
executive committees to pursue further negotiations with the 
intent of devising a means by which the administration and 
operations of the two exchanges could be consolidated most 
efficiently 
essentially theyve agreed on a governing body if there would 
be a merger and the two executive committees are going to continue 
talks said nymex spokeswoman nachamah jacobovits 
spokespeople for both exchanges refused to say why the markets 
were considering a merger or what the benefits of such a 
consolidation would be 
the two exchanges reportedly have discussed the possibility of a 
merger several times over the last decade 
nymex and comex which have been housed in the same lower 
manhattan facility since 1933 trade a variety of commodities 
including oil gold silver copper and aluminum 
the joint body will include a chairman who is a nymex member a 
vice chairman who is a comex member 16 nymex member directors 
eight comex member directors and six public directors 
many of the terms upon which the consolidation would occur 
including the extent and basis upon which either exchanges liquid 
capital reserves would be made available to the consolidated 
entity remain to be determined the statement read 
the two exchanges also said any agreement reached by the 
executive committees and board is subject to membership and 
regulatory approval 
nymex the largest energy exchange trades crude oil heating 
oil unleaded gasoline residual fuel oil propane platinum and 
palladium futures 
comex the most active metals exchange trades gold silver 
copper and aluminum futures comex traded 19 million contracts in 
1989 while nymex traded 385 million 
a futures contract is an agreement to buy or sell a fixed amount 
of a commodity or instrument at a set price on a future date 
