<TEXT>
the new york mercantile exchange and commodity 
exchange inc said wednesday they were exploring a merger of the 
two markets a combination that analysts said could give the comex 
the most immediate rewards 
the two commodities markets announced they were pursuing merger 
negotiations and would form a joint board that would govern any 
consolidated company resulting from a merger 
the exchanges which trade a variety of precious metals and 
energy futures said they agreed to form a joint governing board 
after their executive committees met tuesday 
the marketse respective boards instructed their executive 
committees to continue negotiations over the most efficient way to 
consolidate the administration and operations of the exchanges 
analysts said nymex and comex which have been housed in the 
same lower manhattan building since 1933 have discussed merging at 
various times over the last decade 
sharing resources would mean greater efficiency and cost savings 
for both exchanges but particularly for the smaller commodities 
exchange they said 
i see more advantages for comex said evan baron senior 
account executive for elders futures inc its entire trading 
system needs to be overhauled nymex is already more computerized 
and up to the minute 
comex still operates under an antiquated trading system that is 
more vulnerable to fraud he said 
in addition sharing the merc fee revenue appeals to them 
said john azarow vice president and senior energy trader for smith 
barney harris upham amp co 
a marriage of varied products and markets as the much larger 
chicago commodity exchanges have had for years also makes sense 
financially and strategically 
the concept of having diversified products is attractive 
because if one market is quiet another one might be cooking said 
azarow 
while nymex now is the larger more active market that wasnt 
always true at various times in the 1970s and 1980s comex was the 
bigger more active exchange 
comex traded 19 million futures and options contracts last year 
compared with 385 million for nymex 
now is the mercs time in the sun but who knows we could 
have a change in the economic environment and oils could slump 
while the metals markets boom said azarow 
but while current comex volume is down the merc is slowly 
reaching maturation said one analyst who did not want to be 
named except for a proposed new natural gas contract it has 
traded the same products for years he said 
the joint governing body will include a chairman who is a nymex 
member a vice chairman who is a comex member 16 nymex member 
directors eight comex member directors and six public directors 
the exchanges said many of the terms of any consolidation had 
not yet been determined including the extent that either 
exchanges liquid capital reserves woudl be made available to the 
consolidated market 
the two exchanges also said any agreement reached by the 
executive committees and board is subject to membership and 
regulatory approval 
nymex the nations largest energy exchange trades crude oil 
heating oil unleaded gasoline residual fuel oil propane 
platinum and palladium futures 
comex trades gold silver copper and aluminum futures 
a futures contract is an agreement to buy or sell a fixed amount 
of a commodity or instrument at a set price on a future date 
both exchanges also trade options in many products options are 
contracts that permit the owner to buy or sell at a fixed price 
until a specific date 
