saatchi and saatchi first over the wall boasts 
a large poster recently hung on the eastern side of the berlin wall 
it typifies the bravura that helped saatchi amp saatchi co plc 
burst onto the scene in the 1980s and gobble rivals to become the 
worlds largest advertising company 
but that audacity has backfired a foray into consulting 
businesses has been disastrous and costs spiraled out of control 
if the londonbased agency is to recover analysts say it should 
stick to advertising 
after nearly two decades of uninterrupted annual profit growth 
since brothers maurice and charles saatchi founded the company it 
recently reported the first loss about 97 million for the fiscal 
year ended sept 30 
saatchis stock has fallen sharply on londons exchange and the 
company cut its annual dividend 38 percent 
five of the 12 directors have left in the past year and saatchi 
recruited a new chief executive frenchman robert louisdreyfus 
who turned around ims international inc the new yorkbased 
