company inevitably ended up handling rival accounts 
it lost hundreds of millions of dollars in business from the 
consumer products giants procter amp gamble co and colgatepalmolive 
co and others because clients were concerned about 
confidentiality and conflicts of interest 
born in baghdad to a prosperous textile merchant the saatchis 
grew up in hampstead north london maurice was an academic success 
with a sharp business mind charles proved a brilliant copywriter 
they set up their business in 1970 in soho londons ad agency 
heartland and quickly developed a reputation for simple 
provocative ads their 1971 print ad promoting contraception for 
example showed a pregnant man and asked would you be more 
careful if it was you who got pregnant 
the agency became publicly owned within five years and the 
saatchis chose to relinquish ultimate control in exchange for the 
investors money they needed to expand 
the agency came to prominence in 1979 with the advertising 
campaign that helped the conservatives oust the labor party and put 
margaret thatcher in office labor isnt working said one 
poster depicting a long line of unemployed people 
ambitious and selfmade the saatchis embody the thatcherite 
ideals of entrepreneurship and meritocracy the sunday times list 
