fortune at 35 million pounds or 58 million and ranks them tied 
for 178th 
but the saatchis remain foreigners to britains upper crust 
which bristles at their flashy selfcongratulatory style putting 
a billboard on the berlin wall was another example of their 
instinct for the welltimed publicity coup 
to create their megaagency the saatchis embarked on a takeover 
binge that shocked madison avenue and generated much hostility 
against what detractors called creeping saatchiism 
their biggest purchases were ted bates for 450 million dancer 
fitzgerald sample for 75 million and backer and spielvogel for 
56 million all in 1986 that year saatchi became the worlds 
largest ad holding company 
as a result revenues climbed to nearly 700 million in 1986 and 
15 billion in saatchis latest fiscal year from 62 million in 
1982 
it now employs 16600 people in 58 countries and had client 
billings of 135 billion in 1988 giving it control of 5 percent 
of the worldwide advertising market the trade journal advertising 
age said 
saatchi has championed the global translatable campaign like 
its new tv ad for british airways appearing on three continents 
in which 4000 people form a smiling winking face on a vast 
landscape 
to overcome the reluctance of clients to be lumped together with 
their competitors saatchi divided itself into two competing 
international groups saatchi amp saatchi advertising and backer 
spielvogel bates worldwide 
but critics say saatchi overspent on its buying spree took too 
