the explosion occurred after the lid of a 11000gallon sulfuric 
acid tank blew off according to ms mosley sulfuric acid is used 
to manufacture kevlar used in bullet proof vests and nomex used 
in protective clothing for firefighters ms kukura said 
ms mosley said the smoke was confined to the local area and 
there were no evacuations she said officials in salem nj told 
residents to remain indoors when the fire broke out 
the plant is located several miles north of the delaware 
memorial bridge in deepwater a spokeswoman for the delaware river 
and bay authority said bridge traffic was not affected by the 
explosion 
du pont took air samples within an 8mile radius as a 
precaution according to ms mosley she said preliminary results 
did not detect any release of toxins 
the department of environmental protection has not issued any 
violations against du pont ms mosely said she said the agency is 
still investigating the incident 
chambers works is du ponts largest chemical facility about 
3600 employees work at the plant 
</TEXT>
